    17Ôćĺ/**
    18Ôćĺ * DistributeMatchingUnions takes two arguments:
    19Ôćĺ * - a data structure of type `a` containing unions
    20Ôćĺ * - a pattern `p`, matching this data structure
    21Ôćĺ * and turns it into a union of all possible
    22Ôćĺ * combination of each unions contained in `a` that matches `p`.
    23Ôćĺ *
    24Ôćĺ * It does this in 3 main steps:
    25Ôćĺ *  - 1. Find all unions contained in the data structure, that matches `p`
    26Ôćĺ *    with `FindUnions<a, p>`. It returns a tree of [union, path] pairs.
    27Ôćĺ *  - 2. this tree is passed to the `Distribute` type level function,
    28Ôćĺ *    Which turns it into a union of list of `[singleValue, path]` pairs.
    29Ôćĺ *    Each list correspond to one of the possible combination of the unions
    30Ôćĺ *    found in `a`.
    31Ôćĺ *  - 3. build a data structure with the same shape as `a` for each combination
    32Ôćĺ *    and return the union of these data structures.
    33Ôćĺ *
    34Ôćĺ * @example
    35Ôćĺ * type t1 = DistributeMatchingUnions<['a' | 'b', 1 | 2], ['a', 1]>;
    36Ôćĺ * // => ['a', 1] | ['a', 2] | ['b', 1] | ['b', 2]
    37Ôćĺ *
    38Ôćĺ * type t2 = DistributeMatchingUnions<['a' | 'b', 1 | 2], ['a', unknown]>;
    39Ôćĺ * // => ['a', 1 | 2] | ['b', 1 | 2]
    40Ôćĺ */
    41Ôćĺexport type DistributeMatchingUnions<a, p> = IsAny<a> extends true
    42Ôćĺ  ? any
    43Ôćĺ  : BuildMany<a, Distribute<FindUnionsMany<a, p>>>;
    46Ôćĺexport type FindUnionsMany ÔÇŽ
    62Ôćĺ/**
    63Ôćĺ * The reason we don't look further down the tree with lists,
    64Ôćĺ * Set and Maps is that they can be heterogeneous,
    65Ôćĺ * so matching on a A[] for a in input of (A|B)[]
    66Ôćĺ * doesn't rule anything out. You can still have
    67Ôćĺ * a (A|B)[] afterward. The same logic goes for Set and Maps.
    68Ôćĺ *
    69Ôćĺ * Kinds are types of types.
    70Ôćĺ *
    71Ôćĺ * kind UnionConfig = {
    72Ôćĺ *  cases: Union<{
    73Ôćĺ *    value: b,
    74Ôćĺ *    subUnions: UnionConfig[]
    75Ôćĺ *  }>,
    76Ôćĺ *  path: string[]
    77Ôćĺ * }
    78Ôćĺ * FindUnions :: Pattern a p => a -> p -> UnionConfig[]
    79Ôćĺ */
